==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: cedilla
<hw>ce*dil"la</hw> <pr>(s⟦esl⟧*d⟦icr⟧l"l⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Sp. <ets>cedilla</ets>, cf. F. <ets>c⟦eacute⟧dille</ets>; dim. of
<ets>zeta</ets>, the Gr. name of the letter <ets>z</ets>, because this
letter was formerly written after the <ets>c</ets>, to give it the sound
of <ets>s</ets>.]</ety> <def>A mark placed under the letter <xex>c</xex>
[thus, ⟦cced⟧], to show that it is to be sounded like <xex>s</xex>, as
in <xex>fa⟦cced⟧ade</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cedrat</ent>⟦br⟧
